==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thermoelectrometer
<hw>Ther`mo*e`lec*trom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thermo-</ets> + <ets>electrometer</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for measuring the strength of an
electric current in the heat which it produces, or for determining the
heat developed by such a current.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermogen</ent>⟦br⟧
